================================================================================
WHAT IS COVERED BY THE NON-COMMERCIAL LICENSE
================================================================================

The CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license applies to:

✓ Python source code files:
  - coptic-parser.py
  - coptic-parser-simple-wrapper.py
  - app.py (Gradio interface)
  - Any custom scripts in scripts/ directory

✓ Documentation:
  - README.md
  - QUICK_START.md
  - TROUBLESHOOTING.md
  - CONTRIBUTING.md
  - CREDITS_AND_ATTRIBUTION.md
  - All markdown documentation files

✓ GUI and Interface:
  - Tkinter GUI implementation
  - Gradio web interface design
  - Virtual keyboard implementation
  - Visualization code

✓ Training configurations and project-specific models:
  - Model training scripts
  - Configuration files specific to this project

✓ GitHub workflows and project configuration:
  - .github/ directory contents
  - Issue templates
  - Pull request templates

================================================================================
WHAT IS NOT COVERED (THIRD-PARTY DEPENDENCIES)
================================================================================

The following components retain their ORIGINAL LICENSES and are NOT subject
to the CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 restrictions:

Third-party libraries (see LICENSES/ directory for full license texts):
  - Stanford Stanza (Apache 2.0)
  - DiaParser (Apache 2.0)
  - PyTorch (BSD-3-Clause)
  - Gradio (Apache 2.0)
  - NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib (BSD-3-Clause)
  - Other Python dependencies listed in requirements.txt

Training data:
  - Coptic SCRIPTORIUM corpus (see data/ directory for specific licensing)
  - Universal Dependencies treebanks (various Creative Commons licenses)

